#MISSILE INTERCEPTION ADN GUIDANCE SIMULATION
#   A modular Python simulation for modeling target motion, interceptor dynamics, and guidance laws

#OVERVIEW
#   This project implements a modular missile interception simulation designed for research, experimentation, and demonstration of aerospace engineering fundamentals
#   The architecture seperates state representation, guidance logic, vehicle dynamics, and simulation control
#   The simulation will eventually be connected to hardware to point a turret in the direction of the target assuming a rapid acceleration and constant velocity of projectile
#   The goal is to provide a transparent extensible framework for studying:\
#       Target motion modeling
#       Interceptor kinematics and dynamics
#       Proportional navigation and other guidance laws
#       Engagement geometry
#       Simulation loop design
#       Visualization adn analysis of interception performance
#   This project is actively being developed as a part of a larger engineer portfolio

#PROJECT STRUCTURE

#Missile_Interception_Simulation Folder     -Holds Everything

#   main.py                                 -Simulation Entry Point

#   Simulation Folder
#       state.py                            -State vector representation(position, velocity, acceleration)
#       target.py                           -Target motion model
#       interceptor.py                      -Interceptor model (mass, thrust, limits)
#       guidance.py                         -Guidance laws(Proportional Navigation, Augmented Proportional Navigation, Zero Effort Miss, True Proportional Navigation(TPN), Command to Line of Sight(CLOS), etc)
#       dynamics.py                         -3-DOF and eventually 6-DOF equations of motion
#       integrator.py                       -Numerical Integration(Euler(fast rate),Runge-Kutta 4th Order(more accurate - like a taylor series))
#       utils.py                            -Math helpers, coordinate transforms

#   Visualization Folder
#       plot2d.py                           -Plots in 2D
#       plot3d.py                           -Plots in 3D
#       animate.py                          -Animation Tool 

#   Sensors Folder
#       camera.py                           -Grab data from the camera
#       tracking.py                         -Convert camera pixel data to usable data

#   Hardware Folder
#       servo.py                            -Tells servo to move(may add another in the future for camera to move as well)

#   Data Folder
#       Logs Folder                         -Holds logs of data

#   README Text File                        -Documentation of what project is/goal

#   Worklog Folder
#       Multiple Documents                  -Each file is a file for what was worked on that day

#   Sources Text File                       -Single File of all sources and their respective descriptions